    "Room temperature uniaxial tensile tests conducted along rolling direction at strain rate of 10^-3 s^-1 using Instron 5892 with contact extensometer.",
    "Fracture surface morphology: Zr0 steel exhibits small dimples and cleavage faces; Zr0.01 and Zr0.50 steels show larger and deeper dimples with increased density as Zr content increases.",
    "True stress-strain curve of Zr0.50 steel shown as inset in Fig. 4a indicates high true ultimate tensile strength and true strain, but exact values are not provided in text.",
    "Oxygen, nitrogen and hydrogen contents controlled during steelmaking: average O 12–89 ppm, N ~18 ppm, H ~2 ppm.",
    "Fig. 3a table indicates Zr0.50 fine grain area fraction of 34%, while abstract and results text state ~35%.",
    "Grain size distribution data shown in Fig. 3b–d indicates bimodal distribution in Zr0.50 steel (peaks near 1 μm and 5 μm) versus unimodal distributions in Zr0 (~12 μm) and Zr0.01 (~7 μm).",
    "Stacking fault energy of FCC matrix in Zr0.50 estimated to be ~55 mJ/m^2 from supplementary text S1.",
    "EBSD analysis indicates f_CG,b (fraction of CGs adjacent to FGs) is ~37% in Zr0.50 steel.",
